764
00:58:58,451 --> 00:58:59,869
-What is it?
-What's wrong?

765
00:59:00,954 --> 00:59:03,081
Will you please be quiet?

766
00:59:03,665 --> 00:59:04,499
Be silent.

767
00:59:05,625 --> 00:59:07,418
Are you trying to agitate the patients?

768
00:59:08,044 --> 00:59:09,796
Be careful when you use
the word "emergency."

769
00:59:10,088 --> 00:59:13,132
Ms. Ko is here. I think she came
not knowing her class got canceled.

770
00:59:13,716 --> 00:59:17,178
She had this look on her face
and went to find the director.

771
00:59:17,762 --> 00:59:19,847
-Didn't you call her?
-Didn't you?

772
00:59:20,181 --> 00:59:21,724
Why didn't you?

773
00:59:23,017 --> 00:59:24,310
-What?
-You guys are close.

774
00:59:24,394 --> 00:59:25,228
No, they're not!

775
00:59:25,812 --> 00:59:28,606
Wait. Wait a minute.

776
00:59:28,690 --> 00:59:33,069
Does that mean
no one called and told Ms. Ko

777
00:59:33,152 --> 00:59:35,196
that her fairy tale class got canceled?

778
00:59:35,780 --> 00:59:36,948
What's wrong with you?

779
00:59:37,031 --> 00:59:39,867
She found out through the notice board.
She must be furious right now.

780
00:59:39,951 --> 00:59:41,119
I'll go find her.

781
00:59:42,620 --> 00:59:45,415
I used to run marathons when I was young.

782
00:59:45,957 --> 00:59:47,792
But one day, my knees got infected.

783
00:59:48,501 --> 00:59:52,463
I should've gotten some rest,
but I just ran a marathon again.

784
00:59:54,841 --> 00:59:57,760
In the end, my cartilage got ruined,
and I ended up with metal pins.

785
00:59:57,844 --> 00:59:59,804
Now, it's hard for me
to even walk properly.

786
01:00:02,015 --> 01:00:05,727
Don't make the same mistake I did
and try to run when you can't even walk.

787
01:00:11,858 --> 01:00:14,569
When you're tired, get some rest.
When you're sad, go ahead and cry.

788
01:00:16,696 --> 01:00:18,656
It's okay to take a break.

789
01:00:19,240 --> 01:00:20,325
Then one day,

790
01:00:21,701 --> 01:00:24,621
there will surely come a day
when you'll be able to run again.

791
01:00:25,872 --> 01:00:28,291
I bet your daughter is cheering you on.

792
01:00:31,085 --> 01:00:34,213
That darn geezer. How dare he cancel
my class without telling me?

793
01:00:35,590 --> 01:00:36,674
There he is.

794
01:00:37,300 --> 01:00:40,637
Darn, did he take drugs or something?
Why is he so fast?

795
01:00:47,560 --> 01:00:48,394
Ms. Ko!

796
01:00:55,777 --> 01:00:57,028
Wait here for a second.

797
01:00:59,113 --> 01:01:00,448
Let me take you back to your room.

798
01:01:03,868 --> 01:01:04,702
I'm sorry.

799
01:01:07,330 --> 01:01:09,624
I'm guessing I put you
in a difficult position.

800
01:01:10,708 --> 01:01:12,502
You didn't just put me
in a difficult position.

801
01:01:12,919 --> 01:01:14,045
I got fired.

802
01:01:14,837 --> 01:01:15,838
Hey.

803
01:01:16,422 --> 01:01:17,715
How will you compensate for this?

804
01:01:28,810 --> 01:01:29,644
This is expensive.

805
01:01:31,562 --> 01:01:34,315
-I want it.
-But that's...

806
01:01:34,399 --> 01:01:35,483
Let me have this.

807
01:01:38,111 --> 01:01:41,406
You told me you're sorry.
Then you should compensate for the damage.

808
01:01:41,948 --> 01:01:43,449
That's what you call a sincere apology.

809
01:01:53,668 --> 01:01:54,502
Give it back.

810
01:01:58,297 --> 01:01:59,590
Take it.

811
01:02:03,261 --> 01:02:05,263
I've had it for more than enough.

812
01:02:17,400 --> 01:02:18,484
Mr. Moon.

813
01:02:19,819 --> 01:02:20,737
Yes?

814
01:02:21,779 --> 01:02:23,573
The burden is finally gone.

815
01:02:38,171 --> 01:02:39,338
Isn't it hot?

816
01:02:39,964 --> 01:02:41,466
I bet your neck is sweating.

817
01:02:42,133 --> 01:02:45,511
If you want to be fashionable,
you must be uncomfortable and stubborn.

818
01:02:48,848 --> 01:02:50,933
My brother is immersed
in one of your books these days.

819
01:02:51,893 --> 01:02:52,935
I know.

820
01:02:53,478 --> 01:02:54,645
The Cheerful Dog.

821
01:03:01,694 --> 01:03:03,112
"Once upon a time,

822
01:03:03,196 --> 01:03:08,201
there lived a dog that was
very good at hiding his emotions.

823
01:03:09,410 --> 01:03:11,871
The dog was tied beneath a shade tree.

824
01:03:11,954 --> 01:03:14,373
He always wagged his tail and acted cute.

825
01:03:14,457 --> 01:03:17,835
So he got the name, "The Cheerful Dog,"
because he was as cheerful as springtime.

826
01:03:18,127 --> 01:03:22,381
The dog always had lots of fun
with the village kids during the day.

827
01:03:22,632 --> 01:03:23,758
But every night,

828
01:03:23,841 --> 01:03:28,971
he'd moan and whine
when no one was around.

829
01:03:29,680 --> 01:03:34,143
That's because
he wanted to cut off the leash

830
01:03:34,560 --> 01:03:38,523
and freely run around
out in the spring field.

831
01:03:39,023 --> 01:03:41,359
However, he couldn't.

832
01:03:41,442 --> 01:03:44,237
And that's why he cried every night.

833
01:03:44,695 --> 01:03:47,490
Every single night.

834
01:03:48,324 --> 01:03:49,242
One day,

835
01:03:49,325 --> 01:03:53,788
a voice inside him asked the Cheerful Dog.

836
01:03:54,580 --> 01:03:59,544
'Hey, why don't you just cut off the leash
and run away?'

837
01:03:59,627 --> 01:04:02,255
And this is what the Cheerful Dog said..."

838
01:04:03,464 --> 01:04:07,176
"I've been tied up for way too long.

839
01:04:08,719 --> 01:04:10,972
So I forgot how to cut myself free."

840
01:04:24,360 --> 01:04:25,653
You did great, Mun-yeong.

841
01:04:27,738 --> 01:04:28,823
What did I do?

842
01:04:30,074 --> 01:04:31,868
You helped her cut herself free.

843
01:05:02,106 --> 01:05:03,149
You will

844
01:05:06,777 --> 01:05:09,405
end up like your mother.

845
01:05:10,781 --> 01:05:14,660
You won't be able to escape.

846
01:05:17,371 --> 01:05:18,205
No.

847
01:05:20,041 --> 01:05:21,083
I'm different.

848
01:06:35,449 --> 01:06:36,534
Your...

849
01:06:38,577 --> 01:06:40,162
-Your hair--
-I...

850
01:06:40,997 --> 01:06:42,456
cut off my leash.

851
01:06:58,264 --> 01:07:01,517
PATIENT ROOM 201-208

852
01:08:14,090 --> 01:08:15,174
It's all done.

853
01:09:22,616 --> 01:09:23,576
How do I look?

854
01:09:27,121 --> 01:09:28,080
You look pretty.

855
01:09:59,069 --> 01:10:01,947
SPECIAL THANKS TO BAE HAE-SUN
FOR MAKING A GUEST APPEARANCE

856
01:10:39,526 --> 01:10:40,444
I'm very pretty.

857
01:10:41,070 --> 01:10:42,905
I'm just like your brother.

858
01:10:42,988 --> 01:10:44,782
Longer hair suits you better.

859
01:10:44,865 --> 01:10:46,951
Why did she cut it? Why?

860
01:10:47,034 --> 01:10:48,118
Chew on this.

861
01:10:48,702 --> 01:10:50,454
Why do you think she lied?

862
01:10:50,537 --> 01:10:53,165
It seems like something strange
is happening at our hospital.

863
01:10:54,041 --> 01:10:55,251
That woman

864
01:10:56,293 --> 01:10:57,294
is dead.

865
01:10:58,045 --> 01:10:59,880
But she's here.

866
01:11:01,131 --> 01:11:02,716
Safety pin and bomb.

867
01:11:02,800 --> 01:11:06,220
You're patient, and I'm volatile.

868
01:11:06,303 --> 01:11:08,055
Could you take a photo of us?

869
01:11:08,264 --> 01:11:11,642
According to Mr. Lee, I sell one more book
every time I smile at a fan.

870
01:11:11,725 --> 01:11:13,352
An author only needs to write well.

871
01:11:13,435 --> 01:11:15,062
She's not a celebrity.

872
01:11:15,145 --> 01:11:17,147
-Are you jealous?
-Jealous, my ass.

873
01:11:20,317 --> 01:11:21,277
"Offer"?

874
01:11:21,944 --> 01:11:24,405
But if I give all my stuff to people
who need them,

875
01:11:26,240 --> 01:11:28,033
what will I have left?

876
01:11:31,328 --> 01:11:33,956
Subtitle translation by Ja-won Lee
